"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78151","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-01","<p>The total number of compulsory and voluntary redundancies that have been issued to employees of the Service Personnel and Veterans Agency in each year since 2010 is set out in the table below.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td colspan="3"><p><strong>Number* of Redundancies from SPVA</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>YEAR</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>COMPULSORY</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>VOLUNTARY</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>TOTAL</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>~</p></td><td><p>9</p></td><td><p>12</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>~</p></td><td> </td><td><p>~</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>~</p></td><td> </td><td><p>~</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>TOTAL</p></td><td><p>8</p></td><td><p>9</p></td><td><p>17</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>* In line with departmental policy ~ Represents 5 or fewer</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-09-01T12:56:44.6448111Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78151/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78151/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78151/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Service Personnel and Veterans Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) compulsory and (b) voluntary redundancies have been issued to employees of the Service Personnel and Veterans Agency in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206075"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78152","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-01","<p>The key performance indicator for the Armed Forces Pensions Scheme is to make 99.3% of all Service pension payments (including new awards) by the due date. This has been achieved in each year since 2010.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-09-01T16:48:56.728253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78152/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78152/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78152/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Armed Forces: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the average length of time taken to process settlements for the Armed Forces Pension Scheme has been in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206083"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78153","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-13","<p>The Armed Forces Pension Scheme is an occupational pension scheme. Payments are made using calculations based on a Service person’s salary and number of years service.</p><p> </p><p>It would give a false impression to give an answer based on a mathematical calculation of dividing the annual expenditure by the number of Pension members. It is therefore not appropriate to provide an average individual pay out and individual financial settlement.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Number* of payments</p></td><td><p>Total paid out</p><p>£ millions</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>377,325 Pensions &amp; dependants</p><p>10,455 Lump Sum</p></td><td><p>3,519</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>383,490 Pensions &amp; dependants</p><p>11,945 Lump Sum</p></td><td><p>3,811</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>390,040 Pensions &amp; dependants</p><p>12,950 Lump Sum</p></td><td><p>4,071</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>396,603 Pensions &amp; dependants</p><p>13,175 Lump Sum</p></td><td><p>4,089</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>* in line with Defence Statistics rounding policy all figures have been rounded to the nearest 5</p><p> </p><p>The Armed Forces Pension Scheme is an occupational pension scheme. Payments are made using calculations based on a Service person’s salary and number of years service.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-13T16:00:33.138282Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78153/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78153/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78153/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Armed Forces: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the average (a) individual payout and (b) individual financial settlement under the Armed Forces Pension Scheme has been in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206084"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78154","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-02","<p> </p><p>It is not possible to provide the value of payouts made to Armed Forces veterans and their families under the War Pensions Scheme as a result of service in Afghanistan as the information is not held in a format that would enable us to easily answer the question and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-09-02T14:25:39.8186352Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78154/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78154/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78154/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Afghanistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the total value of payouts to armed forces veterans and their families under the War Pensions Scheme as a result of service in Afghanistan has been in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206077"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78155","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-08-04","<p> </p><p>Claims for damages brought against the Ministry of Defence (MOD) are not recorded in a manner that enables us to identify those for injuries received specifically in the course of training without incurring disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","206070","2014-08-04T10:22:42.7684285Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78155/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78155/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78155/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Armed Forces: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many compensation pay outs of what value have been issued by his Department on the grounds of personnel sustaining injuries through training in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206065"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78156","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-02","<p>The total expenditure to Armed Forces veterans and their families under the War Pensions Scheme in each year since 2010 has been;<br><br>2010-11 - £ 935 million<br>2011-12 - £ 916 million<br>2012-13 - £ 908 million<br>2013-14 - £ 859 million</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-09-02T14:26:26.8528231Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78156/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78156/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78156/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","War Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the total value of payouts to armed forces veterans and their families under the War Pensions Scheme has been in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206078"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78157","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-13","<p>The War Pensions Scheme provides no fault compensation for Service personnel disabled as a result of their service in HM Forces where the cause of the injury, disability or disease is before 6 April 2005, whether or not the condition was sustained during a conflict. The table sets out the total number of claims and total amount of payments. It would give a false impression to give an answer based on a mathematical calculation of dividing the annual expenditure by the number of recipients.</p><p> </p><p>Each award is specific to the individual and assessments are made based on an individual’s level of disability at any one time. Should the accepted condition deteriorate, the recipient may request a review of the level of their assessment. War Pension entitlement is given for life and the percentage assessment of each accepted condition changes as the level of disability deteriorates or improves over an individual’s lifetime.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Number* of payments</p></td><td><p>Total paid out</p><p>£ millions</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>142,485 Disablement pensioners</p><p>28,425 War Widows</p><p>3,260 Lump Sum Gratuities</p></td><td><p>£935</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>135,160 Disablement pensioners</p><p>26,375 War Widows</p><p>2,865 Lump Sum Gratuities</p></td><td><p>£916</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>128,280 Disablement pensioners</p><p>24,415 War Widows</p><p>2,600 Lump Sum Gratuities</p></td><td><p>£908</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>121,940 Disablement pensioners</p><p>22,260 War Widows</p><p>4,120 Lump Sum Gratuities</p></td><td><p>£859</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>* in line with Defence Statistics rounding policy all figures have been rounded to the nearest 5</p><p> </p><p>In addition to a War Disablement Pension, some veterans may be eligible for a range of supplementary allowances such as Constant Attendance Allowance, Unemployability Supplement, Allowance for Lowered Standard of Occupation or War Pensioners Mobility Supplement. These allowances mirror the benefits payable by the Department for Work and Pensions but are tax free and paid at a slightly more generous rate. Entitlement to these allowances is determined by individual circumstance and level of disability. These allowances are not included in the number of payments listed above.</p><p> </p><p>Each war pension award is specific to the individual and assessments are made based on an individual’s level of disability at any one time. Should the accepted condition deteriorate over time, the recipient may request a review of their assessment. The above information gives an average individual payout per annum, it does not give an overall ‘settlement’.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-13T15:57:58.4039468Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78157/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78157/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78157/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","War Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the average average (a) individual payout and (b) individual financial settlement under the War Pension Scheme has been in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206085"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78158","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-02","<p>The total expenditure to Armed Forces veterans and their families under the Armed Forces Pension Scheme each year since 2010 has been;<br><br>2010-11 - £ 3,519 million<br>2011-12 - £ 3,811 million<br>2012-13 - £ 4,071 million<br>2013-14 - £ 4,089 million</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-09-02T14:24:16.9548489Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78158/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78158/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78158/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Armed Forces: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the total value of payouts to armed forces veterans and their families under the Armed Forces Pension scheme has been in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206079"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78159","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-08-07","<p>The decision to extend the Sentinel long-range airborne surveillance aircraft until 2018 was made in the Department’s most recent financial planning cycle. The decision was taken to preserve a capability to conduct wide area surveillance of operational environments in the short term, and to allow the longer-term requirement to be considered during the next Strategic Defence and Security Review.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-08-07T10:50:28.682059Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78159/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78159/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78159/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when it was decided that his Department would maintain the use of the Sentinel aircraft until 2018; and what the reasons were for this decision.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206091"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78160","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-22","<p>It is the long standing policy of Her Majesty's Government to not ordinarily comment on UK Special Forces.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2014-07-22T17:06:15.5559841Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78160/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78160/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78160/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Special Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Special Forces personnel there were in each regiment in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206092"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78161","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-08-04","<p> </p><p>Claims for damages brought against the Ministry of Defence (MOD) are not recorded in a manner that enables us to identify those for injuries received specifically in the course of training without incurring disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","206065","2014-08-04T10:22:42.9559873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78161/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78161/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78161/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Armed Forces: Injuries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the value of payouts has been in each year since 2010 to forces personnel and veterans on the grounds of physical injuries.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206070"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78162","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-02","<p> </p><p>It is not possible to provide the value of payouts under the Armed Forces Pension Scheme (AFPS) to forces personnel and veterans on the grounds of physical injuries as the information requested is not held in a format that would enable us to easily answer the question and could only be provided at disproportionate cost. <br><br>The AFPS is primarily an occupational pension scheme where pension payments may be enhanced where a Service person is medically discharged with a condition caused by Service. The Pension scheme computer system does not hold details of the medical condition for which the enhanced pension is being paid.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-09-02T14:29:03.3313694Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78162/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78162/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78162/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Armed Forces: Injuries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the value of payouts under the Armed Forces Pensions Scheme to forces personnel and veterans on the grounds of physical injuries has been in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206071"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78163","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-02","<p> </p><p>It is not possible to provide the value of payouts under the Armed Forces Pension Scheme (AFPS) to forces personnel and veterans on the grounds of mental ill health as the information requested is not held in a format that would enable us to easily answer the question and could only be provided at disproportionate cost. <br><br>The AFPS is primarily an occupational pension scheme where pension payments may be enhanced where a Service person is medically discharged with a condition caused by Service. The Pension scheme computer system does not hold details of the medical condition for which the enhanced pension is being paid.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-09-02T14:27:39.3720719Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78163/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78163/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78163/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Armed Forces: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the value of payouts under the Armed Forces Pensions Scheme to forces personnel and veterans on the grounds of mental ill health has been in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206072"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78164","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-01","<p>A Twitter account run by the Department is a Twitter account that has been registered either by the Ministry of Defence (MOD) or one of the single services (either corporate or sponsored accounts). The MOD currently runs 109 Twitter accounts.</p><p> </p><p>Spending on Twitter accounts includes money paid to Twitter in Financial Year (FY) 2013-14. See table.</p><p> </p><p>Spending on all social media includes money paid to other social media channels directly during FY 2013-14. The MOD spent £87,206 on Twitter in FY 2013-14 and £767,981.89 on all Social Media. See table.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-09-01T13:02:39.4037715Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78164/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78164/answer","HOC.206050.doc","Spending on Twitter accounts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78164/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Social Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Twitter accounts are run by his Department; how much his Department spends annually on (a) Twitter accounts and (b) all social media; and how many people in his Department are employed to work on social media.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206050"
