"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78167","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-08-04","<p> </p><p>Claims for damages brought against the Ministry of Defence (MOD) specifically by victims of road traffic accidents are not recorded in a manner that enables us to identify them without incurring disproportionate cost. The amounts paid as a result of claims brought by third parties against the MOD arising out of road traffic accidents, including legal costs, since 2010 were as follows:</p><p> </p><p>Amount paid</p><p>2010-11 £6 million</p><p>2011-12 £5 million</p><p>2012-13 £4 million</p><p>2013-14 £3 million</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-08-04T10:21:07.0368667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78167/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78167/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78167/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Roads: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department has paid in compensation to victims of road traffic accidents in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206069"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78168","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-08-07","<p> </p><p>The cost to keep Sentinel aircraft in service in each year until 2018 is shown in the table:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>2017-18</p></td><td><p>2018-19</p></td><td><p>Total</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£ millions</p></td><td><p>63.541</p></td><td><p>54.644</p></td><td><p>45.054</p></td><td><p>35.158</p></td><td><p>198.398</p><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-08-07T10:52:02.3589747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78168/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78168/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78168/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much will it cost his Department to keep Sentinel aircraft in service in each year until 2018","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206089"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78169","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-08-07","<p> </p><p>The E-Scan Radar Development Programme for Typhoon is currently still within the Assessment Phase, prior to its main investment decision. Once this decision has been made an In-Service Date on UK aircraft will be determined.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-08-07T10:52:54.2818797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78169/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78169/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78169/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","European Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when the E-Scan radar for the Eurofighter Typhoon aircraft  (a) was originally expected to come into use and (b) is now expected to come into use.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206090"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78170","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-08-12","<p> </p><p>The £1.1billion package has been funded predominantly by carrying over resources from 2012-13 and 2013-14. It has also been funded by drawing down some of the Ministry of Defence’s unallocated financial provision to the appropriate level in the context of the most recent financial planning cycle, and by reprioritising some existing expenditure within the Defence programme.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-08-12T10:16:05.4513713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78170/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78170/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78170/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the press release from the Prime Minister's Office of 14 July 2014, entitled PM announces £1.1 billion investment in capabilities for the armed forces, whether this amount will be sourced from departmental underspends.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206098"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78171","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-17","<p> </p><p>HMS Protector was built at Havyard AS in Norway in 2001 for GC Rieber. From April 2011 until September 2013, the ship was leased from GC Rieber, to provide the Ministry of Defence (MOD) with an Ice Patrol Ship capability. The annual cost of the lease was £8.7 million, which included the cost of support. <br><br>HMS Protector was purchased by the MOD from GC Rieber for £54 million in September 2013, which included the cost of one year's contract support.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","205665 ; 205666","2014-07-17T16:03:09.630149Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78171/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78171/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78171/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","HMS Protector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department has spent on renting the use of HMS Protector for each year since 2011.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206099"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78172","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-08-07","<p> </p><p>The Ministry of Defence is investing over £100 million in future combat air systems as part of the £1.1 billion investment in capabilities for the Armed Forces.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-08-07T10:55:25.1225296Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78172/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78172/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78172/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the press release from the Prime Minister's Office of 14 July 2014, entitled PM announces £1.1 billion investment in capabilities for the armed forces, how much he plans to invest in unmanned future combat air systems.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206101"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78173","Department for Education","false","2014-07-21","<p>The responsibility for engaging with parents and staff on improving standards in underperforming academies lies with the sponsor or trust.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Education will intervene in cases where we are concerned that sponsors are not bringing about rapid, sustained educational improvements.</p><p> </p><p>In the case of the University of Chester Academies Trust (UCAT), which is the sponsor of the University Academy Liverpool (UAL), the Department has already intervened. Officials have been closely monitoring the performance of the sponsor since the publication of examination results in 2013. In April 2014, my noble Friend Lord Nash issued UCAT with a pre-warning notice letter as a result of our overall concerns about the performance of the Trust and our particular concerns about three of its academies, including UAL. The Trust has responded with an action plan to address these issues.</p><p>We do not tolerate underperformance. Where an academy is not making urgent sustained progress, we will work closely with the school and sponsor to secure whatever changes are necessary to make improvements. This might include a change of leadership, or a new partnership with a successful strong academy, sponsor or school.</p><p> </p><p>We continue to monitor the situation at UAL closely against its action plan and will not hesitate to intervene further at both school and Trust level if results in 2014 do not improve.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson","205793","2014-07-21T15:22:04.423711Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78173/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78173/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78173/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-07-15","University Academy Liverpool","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps her Department has taken to engage with parents and staff at the University Academy, Liverpool, in relation to improving standards.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Mrs Louise Ellman","205791"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78174","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-07-22","<p>The Government has mandated energy suppliers to have completed the rollout of smart meters to all domestic and smaller non-domestic premises by the end of 2020. Energy suppliers are undertaking site surveys and analysing installations completed during the current Foundation stage of the Programme to determine the most effective solutions to reach all premises. As part of the Smart Meter Implementation Programme governance arrangements, an Operational Delivery Group is identifying and agreeing common approaches to installations as a means of ensuring a consistently good consumer experience across the rollout.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-07-22T14:35:28.2199006Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78174/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78174/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78174/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-07-15","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment he has made of the progress made by suppliers and installer of smart meters on finding a solution for hard to install properties.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","205955"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78175","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-07-22","<p>We published an update to the second version of the Smart Metering Equipment Technical Specifications (SMETS2) on July 10 2014. This provides manufacturers with a stable baseline to proceed with development and testing of SMETS2 meters in time for initial DCC operations in Q4 2015.</p><p>Meters compliant with SMETS1 are currently being installed. SMETS1 installations will continue at least until SMETS2 meters are available. We will consult with stakeholders before withdrawing SMETS1.</p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-07-22T14:19:52.7746295Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78175/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78175/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78175/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-07-15","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what contingency plans his Department has in place if the deadline for SMETS 2 is not met.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","206034"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78176","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-07-22","<p>The Biomass Emissions and Counterfactual calculator is due to be published shortly.</p><p> </p>","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd",,"2014-07-22T12:11:42.5907871Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78176/answer","Biography information for Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78176/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78176/answer","Hastings and Rye","Amber Rudd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78176/answer/previousversion/11651","Biography information for Amber Rudd","63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-07-15","Biofuels: Air Pollution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, when he plans to publish his final Biomass Emissions and Counterfactual calculator.","false","Biography information for Julie Elliott","Sunderland Central","Julie Elliott","205947"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78177","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>Defra seeks to protect vulnerable species and to ensure that where abundant or pest species need to be controlled this is done so by legal means.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2014-07-22T09:52:50.248578Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78177/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78177/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78177/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2014-07-15","Nature Conservation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps she is taking to maintain the natural balance of numbers of birds of prey, foxes, magpies, grey-back crows and badgers.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","205772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78178","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-22","<p>The water and sanitation crisis is severe, with 50% of all services down. This situation has been exacerbated by damage to sewerage facilities caused by Israeli airstrikes.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-07-22T14:52:01.1203651Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78178/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78178/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78178/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-15","Middle East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department has taken to substantiate allegations made by Hamas in Gaza that Israel has attacked water wells, water purification plants and sewage treatment plants in Gaza.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","206037"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78179","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-22","<p>Although we do not talk to Hamas, we are aware that they have been under unprecedented political and financial pressure, are isolated and have a strong and active military wing.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-07-22T09:30:52.753781Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78179/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78179/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78179/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-15","Middle East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the reasons why Hamas has orchestrated the firing of rockets at Israel.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","206036"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78180","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-21","<p>All export licence applications are assessed on a case-by-case basis against the Consolidated EU and National Arms Export Licensing Criteria in light of the prevailing circumstances. We will not issue an export licence where we judge there is a clear risk that the proposed export might be used for internal repression. We continue to monitor events in Gaza and Israel carefully and call on all sides to ensure that their actions are in line with international humanitarian law. It is vital that all actions are proportionate and are calibrated to avoid civilian casualties.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-07-21T17:54:23.7021183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78180/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78180/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78180/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-15","Middle East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what guarantees he has sought from Israel that weapons sold to it by the UK will not be used on civilians in Palestine; and what assessment he has made of the reliability of those guarantees.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","205885"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78181","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-21","<p>21 commercial tuna fishing licences were issued by the Britsh Indian Ocean Territory (BIOT) Administration in 2010, prior to the implementation of the Marine Protected Area. Copies will be placed in the Library of the House shortly.</p>","Boston and Skegness","Mark Simmonds",,"2014-07-21T10:30:02.6781093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78181/answer","Biography information for Mark Simmonds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78181/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78181/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-15","British Indian Ocean Territory","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will place in the Library a copy of the commercial tuna-fishing licences sold by the British Indian Ocean Territory Government in 2010.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","205886"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78182","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-22","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) has 17 corporate twitter accounts, including a central @foreignoffice account. The other accounts are for support to British nationals overseas, work on forced marriage, communications in Arabic and Urdu, and a range of other priorities such as recruitment, ending sexual violence in conflict and our policy on Europe. Six Ministers and the Permanent Under Secretary are also on twitter in an official capacity, as well as most of our 270 posts overseas, many of our Ambassadors and some other senior officials. The FCO does not spend anything on its Twitter accounts.</p><p>The FCO runs a range of other social media accounts such as Facebook, Instagram, LinkedIn, Weibo, Flickr, Google+, YouTube but does not pay for any of these.</p><p>The FCO occasionally uses paid-for advertising on its social media channels to promote key content. Any such advertising is subject to Cabinet Office marketing and advertising spending controls and is cleared in line with Cabinet Office procedures. It is not possible to breakdown exact spending, although details of overall exemptions to marketing and advertising controls are available on GOV.UK. https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/exceptions-data</p><p>One FCO official in London maintains the main Foreign Office corporate social media accounts. Staff from across the FCO contribute to other social media channels. For example, a number of staff in our Consular team contribute to the @FCOTravel twitter account as part of our customer service to British Nationals, and staff at posts contribute to overseas channels. It is not possible to give precise numbers across our network as this information is not held centrally and could be obtained only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2014-07-22T15:20:30.1777495Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78182/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78182/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78182/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-15","Social Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many Twitter accounts are run by his Department; how much his Department spends annually on (a) Twitter accounts and (b) all social media; and how many people in his Department are employed to work on social media.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206051"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78183","Department of Health","false","2014-07-22","<p>The decision to outsource or bring services in-house is the responsibility of the Brighton and Sussex University Hospitals NHS Trust Board, which will make these decisions in due course.</p><p> </p><p>We are advised by the NHS Trust Development Authority that the trust has not earmarked beds for the use of private patients. The trust has made a small allowance of 633 square metres of floor area for private patient facilities within the new development (representing 0.68% of the total planned floor area), but not bed capacity. The cost of equipping this area would fall either directly to the trust or a private patient facility operator, and the Trust Board will decide in due course whether to proceed with a private patient facility or an alternative use. We understand that any money generated from private patients would be reinvested to directly benefit National Health Service patients at the hospital.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter","206061","2014-07-22T14:33:35.0202127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78183/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78183/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78183/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Royal Sussex County Hospital","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many and what proportion of the beds and what propotion of the facilities planned under the 3Ts redevelopment of the Royal Sussex County Hospital are planned to be used by private patients; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","206060"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78184","Department of Health","false","2014-07-22","<p>The decision to outsource or bring services in-house is the responsibility of the Brighton and Sussex University Hospitals NHS Trust Board, which will make these decisions in due course.</p><p> </p><p>We are advised by the NHS Trust Development Authority that the trust has not earmarked beds for the use of private patients. The trust has made a small allowance of 633 square metres of floor area for private patient facilities within the new development (representing 0.68% of the total planned floor area), but not bed capacity. The cost of equipping this area would fall either directly to the trust or a private patient facility operator, and the Trust Board will decide in due course whether to proceed with a private patient facility or an alternative use. We understand that any money generated from private patients would be reinvested to directly benefit National Health Service patients at the hospital.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter","206060","2014-07-22T14:33:34.9107883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78184/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78184/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78184/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Royal Sussex County Hospital","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will take steps to ensure that (a) estates maintenance for the Royal Sussex County Hospital remains in-house following the 3Ts redevelopment and (b) (i) catering, (ii) portering, (iii) cleaning and (iv) other soft ancillary services currently outsourced to Sodexo are brought in-house at the end of its contract in 2017 and remain in-house under the redeveloped hospital; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","206061"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78185","Department of Health","false","2014-07-22","<p>The Department has received no reports of ground C abortions which were permitted for reasons of fetal gender between 2003 and 2013.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-07-22T14:06:29.7367399Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78185/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78185/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78185/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what reports his Department has received  of ground C abortions which were permitted for reasons of fetal gender in the last 10 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","206102"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78186","Department of Health","false","2014-07-21","<p>The number of claims notified to the NHS Litigation Authority which have been identified as relating to sexual abuse within the National Health Service in each year since 2010 are as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Number of claims (clinical and non-clinical)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>44</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>15</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>23</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>50</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-07-21T15:42:10.6791982Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78186/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78186/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78186/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","NHS: Sexual Offences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many claims of sexual abuse within the NHS were made to the NHS Litigation Authority in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","206094"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78187","Department of Health","false","2014-07-21","<p>Currently we do not centrally hold data on the number of training places commissioned for mental health talking therapists.</p><p> </p><p>The following table shows the number of Improving Access to Psychological Therapies (IAPT) therapists trained over the last five years, reflecting the needs of a rapidly expanding service, especially to meet demand in the early years.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Total numbers trained</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008-09</p></td><td><p>997</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009-10</p></td><td><p>1,731</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>1,140</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>538</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>528</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>635</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Totals</p></td><td><p>5,569</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p><p><em>Source</em>: NHS England</p><p> </p><p>Health Education England is working with NHS England, to ensure that there are sufficient therapists and other staff with the right skills to support the delivery of the IAPT programme.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-07-21T16:36:28.5095089Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78187/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78187/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78187/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many training places for mental health talking therapists were (a) commissioned and (b) filled in each of the last five years as part of the Improving Access to Psychological Therapies programme.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","206095"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78188","Department of Health","false","2014-07-21","<p>The additional 4,200 health visitors being delivered by 2015 will be offered training so they can detect the early signs of postnatal depression and ensure all women get support during and after birth.</p><p> </p><p>In addition to their core training, health visitors are able to enhance their skills and knowledge in the context of their specific roles. Earlier this year, we commissioned the training of 375 perinatal mental health champions who have now been trained across England. The perinatal champions have responsibility for cascading their training in their local areas - to facilitate the spread of knowledge and practice among colleagues. In addition to the training of champions, all health visitors are able to access perinatal mental health e-learning modules.</p><p> </p><p>The Maternal Mental Health Pathway<sup>1</sup> was developed by health visitors and midwives and is a woman and family-centred approach that facilitates good communication between all those involved in care. It includes auditable referral systems/pathways between acute, primary and specialist care from antenatal period through to the postnatal period.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><sup>1</sup>Published by the Department of Health, August 2012</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-07-21T15:47:41.3403584Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78188/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78188/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78188/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Postnatal Depression","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what training health visitors receive to (a) detect, (b) refer and (c) support women with Postnatal Depression.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","206096"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78189","Department of Health","false","2014-07-21","<p>NHS England has undertaken some initial analysis of the causes of poorer survival rates in older people. This suggests that several issues contribute to poorer survival in older adults. These include the fact that the chances of diagnosis at emergency presentation increase with age and that older patients are more likely to have co-morbidity which may impact on survival during and after surgery. There is also some evidence that access to surgery, chemotherapy and radiotherapy for older patients has historically been worse than for younger patients. Previous work by the National Cancer Equality Initiative and the National Cancer Information Network has identified that cancer treatment rates decline with age.</p><p> </p><p>The International Cancer Benchmarking Partnership has sought to understand how and why cancer survival varies between countries, including among older people. The partnership has generated insight and understanding that will help all partners improve cancer survival outcomes by optimising cancer policies and services.</p><p> </p><p>Evidence from this initiative suggests that late diagnosis and treatment are crucial factors in England having lower survival rates than other comparable countries (i.e. countries with good data collection systems and similar levels of development). We also know that the most important reasons for late diagnosis are low awareness of the signs and symptoms of cancer; and delays in patients presenting to their doctors.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-07-21T16:25:08.3033674Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78189/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78189/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78189/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Cancer: Older People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what research (a) his Department and (b) NHS England is undertaking into comparative cancer survival rates for older people in the UK and other European countries.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","205945"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78190","Department of Health","false","2014-07-21","<p>The NHS Serious Incident Framework issued by NHS England in March 2013 updated the National Framework for reporting and learning from serious incidents requiring investigation. It explains the responsibilities for actions and investigations following serious incidents, these include incidents where there may have been shortcomings in NHS-funded care prior to homicides committed by those receiving mental health care services.</p><p> </p><p>The NHS Serious Incident Framework is currently under review, to improve alignment and consistency of serious incident management and to provide further clarity to the NHS about principles, processes and expectations in response to serious incidents. As part of this work, NHS England is keen to develop systems to ensure that investigations are managed in a robust and transparent way. This includes ensuring that the carers and family members of both victims and perpetrators are supported from the onset, including being fully involved in the investigation process and the subsequent action planning and response.</p><p> </p><p>The framework will be published in autumn 2014 and will be implemented by spring 2015.</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","205925 ; 205926","2014-07-21T14:27:43.5494109Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78190/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78190/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78190/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Mental Illness: Homicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to support NHS bodies in assisting the families of those killed by people suffering from mental illness.","false","Biography information for Fabian Hamilton","Leeds North East","Fabian Hamilton","206063"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78191","Department of Health","false","2014-07-21","<p>Ministers have had no recent meetings with either representatives of manufactures of homeopathic medicines or organisations representing homeopathic practitioners.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-07-21T14:08:13.1347748Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78191/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78191/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78191/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Homeopathy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent meetings Ministers his Department have held with (a) representatives of manufacturers of homeopathic medicines and (b) organisations representing homeopathic practitioners.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","205942"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78192","Department of Health","false","2014-07-21","<p>My Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State has had no recent discussions with the Chief Medical Officer on the efficacy of homeopathy.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-07-21T15:54:21.5079422Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78192/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78192/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78192/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Homeopathy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent discussions he has had with the Chief Medical Officer on the efficacy of homeopathy.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","205943"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78193","Department of Health","false","2014-07-22","<p>We have made no such estimate.</p><p> </p><p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) has appraised bivalirudin in combination with aspirin and clopidogrel and recommends the drug as a possible treatment for adults with ST-segment elevation myocardial infarction undergoing primary percutaneous coronary intervention in guidance issued in July 2011.</p><p> </p><p>Patients have the right to drugs and treatments that have been recommended by NICE technology appraisal guidance for use in the National Health Service, where their doctor believes they are clinically appropriate.</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","206058","2014-07-22T14:07:10.5296827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78193/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78193/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78193/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Anticoagulants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will estimate the amount that the NHS would have saved if the anti-coagulant drug Heparin were used instead of Bivalirudin during cardiac procedures in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","206057"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78194","Department of Health","false","2014-07-22","<p>As at 16 July 2014, 107 of the 131 (82%) Director of Public Health posts are filled by substantive roles. The 131 posts cover 152 local authorities, as some have agreed joint/shared arrangements. There are currently 24 positions vacant (18%). All vacancies are covered by interim/acting arrangements with the exception of one recently vacant post where Public Health England (PHE) is working actively with the council to secure interim arrangements.</p><p> </p><p>Of the 24 current vacancies, 15 are under active recruitment in which adverts have been released and/or interview dates set, and nine are the subject to discussion between PHE and the local authority on the development and approval of a job description.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-07-22T14:39:14.079588Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78194/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78194/answer","PQ206055 - Hansard Extract.docx","Hansard Extract","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78194/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Public Health: Local Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to the Answer on 21 November 2013, what estimate he has made of the number of local authorities currently employing acting or interim directors of public health; and what steps he is taking to fill such posts on a more permanent basis.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","206055"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78195","Department of Health","false","2014-07-21","<p>The Department does not maintain information about those organisations who have been approached and reject joining the Deal, and the reasons for any rejection.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-07-21T14:21:20.5967773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78195/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78195/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78195/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Health: Business","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, which organisations were approached by his Department to join the Responsibility Deal; which such organisations rejected joining the Deal; and what the reasons were for each such rejection.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","206053"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78196","Department of Health","false","2014-07-22","<p>The Government has mandated Health Education England (HEE) to provide national leadership on education, training and workforce development in the National Health Service. This mandate includes a commitment that HEE will ensure that midwifery training produces midwives with the required competencies to practise in the NHS.</p><p>In the Mandate from the Government to HEE for the period from April 2013 to March 2015 the Government has stated that HEE should work with NHS England and others to ensure that sufficient midwives and other maternity staff are trained and available to provide every woman with personalised one-to-one care throughout pregnancy, childbirth and during the postnatal period.</p><p>HEE is leading on the Personalised Maternity Care Project, which will make recommendations on how women who have mental health or substance misuse support requirements will receive appropriate support from specialised trained midwives.</p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-07-22T14:12:43.9098679Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78196/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78196/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78196/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Foetal Alcohol Syndrome","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of training for midwives on foetal alcohol syndrome.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","206054"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78197","Department of Health","false","2014-07-22","<p>We have made no such estimate.</p><p> </p><p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) has appraised bivalirudin in combination with aspirin and clopidogrel and recommends the drug as a possible treatment for adults with ST-segment elevation myocardial infarction undergoing primary percutaneous coronary intervention in guidance issued in July 2011.</p><p> </p><p>Patients have the right to drugs and treatments that have been recommended by NICE technology appraisal guidance for use in the National Health Service, where their doctor believes they are clinically appropriate.</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","206057","2014-07-22T14:07:10.6390099Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78197/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78197/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78197/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Anticoagulants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the cost-effectiveness of the anti-coagulant drug Bivalirudin.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","206058"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78198","Department of Health","false","2014-07-21","<p>The Government intends that broadly the same number of individuals will be entitled to free prescriptions, free eye tests and free dental care, via Universal Credit as are entitled via current qualifying benefits or tax credits. There are roughly 6 million people in England currently on these benefits, and consequently entitled to free prescriptions, free eye tests and free dental care.</p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-07-21T16:25:58.5216574Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78198/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78198/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78198/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 3 July 2014, Official Report, column 712W, on universal credit, how many claimants will be able to access free prescriptions, eye tests and dental care once universal credit has been fully rolled out.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","205938"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78199","Department of Health","false","2014-07-21","<p>The Department does not collect data regarding the time taken for individuals to be assessed for NHS Continuing Healthcare. The National Framework for NHS Continuing Healthcare and NHS-funded Nursing Care sets out that the time which elapses between completion of the Checklist (or other notification of potential eligibility) being received by the relevant clinical commissioning group, and a funding decision being made should, in most cases, not exceed 28 days.</p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-07-21T14:29:20.3252542Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78199/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78199/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78199/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Continuing Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the average time taken is in each health authority from a person being referred for a NHS Continuing Healthcare assessment to the eligibility decision being made.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian Lucas","205868"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78200","Department of Health","false","2014-07-21","<p>Information on spending on wheelchairs and wheelchair vouchers by each clinical commissioning group is not held centrally. Information on spending on wheelchairs and wheelchair vouchers by primary care trusts prior to 31 March 2013 is not held centrally.</p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-07-21T14:31:23.4622803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78200/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78200/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78200/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Wheelchairs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much was spent on wheelchairs and wheelchair vouchers by each clinical commissioning group in each of the last four years.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian Lucas","205869"
