"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77666","Home Office","false","2014-07-30","<p>The Permanent Secretary commissioned an Independent Investigation to determine what material the Department had received in respect of child sexual abuse, including any from Geoffrey Dickens. Copies of the Executive Summary of that review and the Terms of Reference were deposited in the House Library on 31 July 2013. On 7 July the Home Secretary announced that Peter Wanless would lead a review into this investigation under the Terms of Reference that have been agreed, a copy of which is available in the House Library. The review is expected to conclude within 8-10 weeks and a full report of the review report will be published.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker","205646","2014-07-30T12:37:04.135698Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77666/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77666/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77666/answer","Lewes","Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77666/answer/previousversion/10959","Biography information for Norman Baker","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-14","Children: Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will ensure that the review by Peter Wanless will include any actions or discussions of government departments other than the Home Office in respect of the handling of the Geoffrey Dickens files.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","205645"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77667","Home Office","false","2014-07-30","<p>The Permanent Secretary commissioned an Independent Investigation to determine what material the Department had received in respect of child sexual abuse, including any from Geoffrey Dickens. Copies of the Executive Summary of that review and the Terms of Reference were deposited in the House Library on 31 July 2013. On 7 July the Home Secretary announced that Peter Wanless would lead a review into this investigation under the Terms of Reference that have been agreed, a copy of which is available in the House Library. The review is expected to conclude within 8-10 weeks and a full report of the review report will be published.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker","205645","2014-07-30T12:37:04.2486631Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77667/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77667/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77667/answer","Lewes","Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77667/answer/previousversion/10963","Biography information for Norman Baker","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-14","Children: Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether her Department holds any information indicating that the Geoffrey Dickens files were shared with or seen by any other government department.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","205646"
