"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77678","Home Office","false","2014-08-04","<p>The budgeted cost of COMPASS Contracts was determined using actual per place unit costs derived through the competitive procurement process. The actual per place unit rates are commercially sensitive. Disclosure will prejudice the commercial interests of the Department and its suppliers.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-08-04T15:31:00.4749744Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77678/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77678/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77678/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-14","Compass Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the (a) budgeted and (b) actual per place unit cost estimated by her Department is for the COMPASS asylum housing contracts allocated to (i) G4S and (ii) Serco for the period of the contract.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","205544"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77679","Home Office","false","2014-07-30","<p>The information requested relates to a former National Health Service organisation. The Department of Health has confirmed that this information is <br>not available.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-07-30T12:38:24.0457616Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77679/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77679/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77679/answer","Lewes","Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77679/answer/previousversion/10955","Biography information for Norman Baker","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-14","Child Abuse in Cleveland Judicial Inquiry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, where in the public domain the Northern Regional Health Authority report of October 1988 entitled, Action Taken Following the Report of the Judicial Inquiry into Child Abuse in Cleveland may be found; if she will place a copy of this document in the Library; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","205539"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77680","Home Office","false","2014-07-30","<p>The Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) was launched in December 2012. The annual salary of the Chief Executive is £124,230, which is not <br>performance-related. Performance of the management team is a matter for the DBS board. Operational performance is considered by Ministers<br>on a regular basis.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-07-30T16:06:35.8238321Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77680/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77680/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77680/answer","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77680/answer/previousversion/10952","Biography information for Karen Bradley","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-14","Disclosure and Barring Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the annual salary is of the Chief Executive of the Disclosure and Barring Service; what element of that salary is performance-related; and what assessment she has made of the performance of the management team at the disclosure and barring service in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","205540"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77681","Home Office","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p> </p><p>Her Majesty's Passport Office (HMPO) criteria for compensation is set out at: <br>https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/hm-passport-office/about/complaints-<br>procedure. <br>Detailed guidance is available at: <br>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/118588<br>/compensation-complaints-handling.pdf<br><br>HMPO only normally offer compensation for financial loss as a result of delays <br>in their guaranteed (Fast Track and Premium) services. HMPO does not have an <br>estimate of how much compensation may be paid this year in line with their <br>policy. As the Home Secretary announced on 12 June 2014, customers who need to <br>travel within 7 days and who have waited more than three weeks for a <br>straightforward application to be processed through no fault of their own, are <br>fast-tracked free of charge.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-07-22T14:48:21.6347865Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77681/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77681/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77681/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77681/answer/previousversion/10949","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-14","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what her policy is on compensating people who have suffered financial loss as a result of delays by HM Passport Office; and how much compensation her Department expects to pay in such fashion.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","205515"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77682","Home Office","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p> </p><p>Her Majesty's Passport Office (HMPO) criteria for compensation is set out at: <br>https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/hm-passport-office/about/complaints-<br>procedure. <br>Detailed guidance is available at: <br>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/118588<br>/compensation-complaints-handling.pdf<br><br>HMPO only normally offer compensation for financial loss as a result of delays <br>in their guaranteed (Fast Track and Premium) services. HMPO does not have an <br>estimate of how much compensation may be paid this year in line with their <br>policy. As the Home Secretary announced on 12 June 2014, customers who need to <br>travel within 7 days and who have waited more than three weeks for a <br>straightforward application to be processed through no fault of their own, are <br>fast-tracked free of charge.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-07-22T14:48:55.4102781Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77682/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77682/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77682/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77682/answer/previousversion/10950","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-14","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what criteria her Department will apply to compensating individuals who have experienced financial loss following recent delays by HM Passport Office delays.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","205516"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77683","Home Office","false","2014-07-17","<p> </p><p>No assessment has been made of the effectiveness of mobile scooter safety <br>schemes run by police forces. This is an operational matter for chief officers <br>of police. Relevant guidance is also set out in the Highway Code.</p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-07-17T14:15:52.2309443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77683/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77683/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77683/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-14","Invalid Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the efficacy of scooter safety schemes run by police forces for mobile scooter users.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","205502"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77684","Home Office","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p> </p><p>It has not been possible to answer this question because of the disproportionate cost involved in checking through over approximately 15,000 individual staff records.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-07-21T15:23:56.3497121Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77684/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77684/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77684/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-07-14","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many officials employed by her Department, of each grade, have remained at that grade since 2010 but received a pay rise; and how much of a rise each such person at each such grade has received.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","205459"
