"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77726","Scotland Office","false","2014-07-21","<p>The Scotland Office does not employ staff directly. All staff that join do so on an assignment, loan or secondment from other Public Sector bodies, principally the Scottish Government and the Ministry of Justice, who remain the employers. Staff terms and conditions of service, including pay awards and payroll administration is a matter for the parent employers. The office does not hold information in the form requested.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2014-07-21T13:13:47.481222Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77726/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77726/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77726/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-07-14","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many officials employed by his Department, of each grade, have remained at that grade since 2010 but received a pay rise; and how much of a rise each such person at each such grade has received.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","205465"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77727","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","false","2014-07-24","<p> </p><p>The Electoral Commission informs me that its 2013 winter tracker survey provides the most recent public opinion data on satisfaction with the process of voting in Great Britain and Northern Ireland. This research found that nearly three in four (72%) were very or fairly satisfied with the process of voting. Seven per cent were very or fairly dissatisfied. The remainder said that they were ‘Neither satisfied nor dissatisfied’ (18%) or ‘Didn’t know’ (2%).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The full topline findings are available on the Commission’s website at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/our-work/our-research/public-opinion-surveys" target="_blank">http://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/our-work/our-research/public-opinion-surveys</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Commission’s May 2014 post-election public opinion survey, which contains a question on satisfaction with the procedure for voting, will also be published on the same section of the website shortly.</p><p> </p>","South West Devon","Mr Gary Streeter",,"2014-07-24T13:34:35.5244859Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77727/answer","Biography information for Sir Gary Streeter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77727/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77727/answer",,,,,"36","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","2014-07-14","Electoral Systems","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for South West Devon, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, what proportion of the public were (a) satisfied and (b) dissatisfied with the process of voting in Great Britain and Northern Ireland in the most recent year for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","205495"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77728","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-17","<p> </p><p>Under Schedule 4 of the Track Access Agreements between Network Rail and the train operating companies, Network Rail compensates train operators on a formula basis for the estimated overall cost impact of network possessions. It is the train operator that is responsible for providing and meeting the cost of any rail replacement bus services, not Network Rail.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","205527","2014-07-17T14:33:37.9008544Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77728/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77728/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77728/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-14","Railways: Bus Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much Network Rail has paid to First Bus, its subsidiaries or companies where First Bus has an ownership stake for the provision of rail replacement bus services in each train operating company area during disruption caused during the recent winter storms.","false","Biography information for Heidi Alexander","Lewisham East","Heidi Alexander","205526"
